\par
Bootstrap Disabled and Active Items within List Group\par
Tip: In case of list group with linked items, the .disabled class only make the link look like disabled, but the link is still clickable. To actually disable links you need to remove the anchor's href attribute either using the JavaScript or manually.\par
\par
Edge-to-Edge List Groups\par
You can optionally add the class .list-group-flush to the list-group element to remove outer borders and rounded corners to create list groups that are edge-to-edge with their parent container.\par
\par
Let's check out the following example to understand how it actually works:\par
\par
ExampleTry this code \f0\'bb\par
<ul class="list-group list-group-flush w-50">\par
    <li class="list-group-item">Pictures</li>\par
    <li class="list-group-item">Documents</li>        \par
    <li class="list-group-item">Music</li>\par
    <li class="list-group-item">Videos</li>\par
</ul>\par
