Bootstrap Edge-to-Edge List Group\par
Creating Numbered List Groups\par
You can also create list groups where items are numbered through simply adding the modifier class .list-group-numbered on the .list-group element, like this:\par
\par
ExampleTry this code \f0\'bb\par
<ol class="list-group list-group-numbered w-50">\par
    <li class="list-group-item">An item</li>\par
    <li class="list-group-item">A second item</li>\par
    <li class="list-group-item">A third item</li>\par
    <li class="list-group-item">A fourth item</li>\par
</ol>\par
\f1\emdash  The output of the above example will look something like this:\par
\par
Bootstrap Numbered List Group\par
Note: Numbers are generated via CSS (as opposed to <ol> element's default browser styling) for better placement inside list group items and to allow for better customization. See the CSS counter-reset and counter-increment properties to learn more about it.\par
\par
List Group with Checkboxes and Radios\par
You can also place Bootstrap's custom checkboxes and radio buttons within the list group items.\par
\par
The following example will create a list group with custom checkboxes:\par
\par
ExampleTry this code \f0\'bb\par
<div class="list-group w-50">\par
    <label class="list-group-item">\par
        <input type="checkbox" class="form-check-input me-1" name="hobbies"> Music\par
    </label>\par
    <label class="list-group-item">\par
        <input type="checkbox" class="form-check-input me-1" name="hobbies"> Travel & Adventure\par
    </label>\par
    <label class="list-group-item">\par
        <input type="checkbox" class="form-check-input me-1" name="hobbies"> Reading\par
    </label>\par
</div>\par
\f1\emdash  The output of the above example will look something like this:\par
\par
Bootstrap List Group with Checkboxes\par
Similarly, you can place custom radio buttons within list group items, like this:\par
\par
ExampleTry this code \f0\'bb\par
<div class="list-group w-50">\par
    <label class="list-group-item">\par
        <input type="radio" class="form-check-input me-1" name="gender"> Male\par
    </label>\par
    <label class="list-group-item">\par
        <input type="radio" class="form-check-input me-1" name="gender"> Female\par
    </label>\par
</div>\par
\f1\emdash  The output of the above example will look something like this:\par
\par
Bootstrap List Group with Radio Buttons\par
You'll learn about custom checkboxes and radio buttons in the Bootstrap custom forms chapter.\par
\par
List Group with Linked Items\par
You can also link list group items with the little change in HTML markup.\par
\par
Just replace the <li> with <a> tag and use <div> element as a parent instead of <ul>. You can also add icons and badges to this list group to make it more elegant. Here's an example:\par
\par
ExampleTry this code \f0\'bb\par
<div class="list-group w-50">\par
    <a href="#" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action active">\par
        <i class="bi-house-fill"></i> Home\par
    </a>\par
    <a href="#" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">\par
        <i class="bi-camera-fill"></i> Pictures\par
        <span class="badge rounded-pill bg-primary float-end">145</span>\par
    </a>\par
    <a href="#" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">\par
        <i class="bi-music-note-beamed"></i> Music\par
        <span class="badge rounded-pill bg-primary float-end">50</span>\par
    </a>\par
    <a href="#" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">\par
        <i class="bi-film"></i> Videos\par
        <span class="badge rounded-pill bg-primary float-end">8</span>\par
    </a>\par
</div>\par
\f1\emdash  The output of the above example will look something like this:\par
