List Group with Custom Content\par
You can also add nearly any HTML within the list groups with the help of flexbox utilities.\par
\par
Here's an example of a linked list group with headings and paragraph.\par
\par
<!DOCTYPE html>\par
<html lang="en">\par
<head>\par
<meta charset="utf-8">\par
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">\par
<title>Bootstrap Linked List Group with Custom Content</title>\par
<link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.0.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">\par
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.0.2/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>\par
</head>\par
<body>\par
<div class="m-4">\par
    <div class="list-group">\par
        <a href="#" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">\par
            <div class="d-flex w-100 justify-content-between">\par
                <h4>Asteroid detected near earth</h4>\par
                <small>1 days ago</small>\par
            </div>\par
            <p>Researchers have detected an asteroid of the size of a football field near earth. This asteroid does not pose any threat to the planet, but it is difficult to be tracked.</p>\par
        </a>\par
        <a href="#" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action active">\par
            <div class="d-flex w-100 justify-content-between">\par
                <h4>Scientists found massive black hole</h4>\par
                <small>2 days ago</small>\par
            </div>\par
            <p>Scientists have found an ultra-bright, supermassive black hole at the center of a distant galaxy, whose mass is about a million times that of our Sun.</p>\par
        </a>\par
        <a href="#" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">\par
            <div class="d-flex w-100 justify-content-between">\par
                <h4>NASA launches solar probe</h4>\par
                <small>3 days ago</small>\par
            </div>\par
            <p>NASA launched a Parker space probe in 2018 with the mission of making observations of the outer corona of the Sun. It is the first-ever mission to "touch" the Sun.</p>\par
        </a>\par
    </div>\par
</div>\par
</body>\par
</html>\f0\par
